TOMY OF FAILURE' ONTARIO MECHANICS' INSTITUTES, 1835-1895.     DISCUSSES THE RISE AND FALL OF MECHANICS' INSTITUTES IN ONTARIO. THEINSTITUTES WERE ORIGINALLY INTENDED TO PROVIDE TECHNICAL EDUCATION FORMECHANICS TO MAKE THEM BETTER WORKERS, BETTER PEOPLE AND BETTER CITIZENS. THEYFAILED IN THIS LARGELY BECAUSE WHAT THE GOVERNMENT INTENDED THEM TO PROVIDEWAS NOT WHAT WAS NEEDED BY THE PEOPLE THAT THEY SERVED. WORKERS ANDAPPRENTICES DID NOT ATTEND CLASSES IN LARGE NUMBERS BECAUSE THEY WERE PROBABLYEXHAUSTED AFTER A 10 OR 11 HOUR DAY. THROUGH LEGISLATION THE INSTITUTES WERECONVERTED TO FREE PUBLIC LIBRARIES